{"id":459509689,"lang":"python3","time":"9Â months, 3Â weeks","timestamp":1614051103,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"72 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/459509689/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"14.4 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def romanToInt(self, s: str) -> int:\n        roman_dict = {'I': 1, 'V': 5, 'X': 10, 'L': 50, 'C': 100, 'D': 500, 'M': 1000}\n        special_dict = {'IV': 4, 'IX': 9, 'XL': 40, 'XC': 90, 'CD': 400, 'CM': 900}\n        s_test = s\n        sum = 0\n        for key in special_dict:\n            if key in s_test:\n                key_count = len(s_test.split(key)) -1\n                sum = sum + key_count * special_dict.get(key, 0)\n                s_test = ''.join(s_test.split(key))\n            else:\n                next\n                \n        s_list = list(s_test)\n        for n in s_list:\n            sum = sum + roman_dict.get(n, 0)\n        return sum  \n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer"}
